Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.00,0:01:11.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFF00FF&\b1}第5季　第8集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.44,0:00:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初  宇宙是一片黑暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the beginning, there was darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.82,0:00:05.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,紧接着一声巨响  混沌初开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then, bang, giving birth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:07.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间  空间和物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to an endless, expanding existence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.45,0:00:09.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始不断膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of time, space and matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.05,0:00:13.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天  我们都在解密这神秘莫测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking the mysterious,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.59,0:00:16.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,令人疯狂的极端之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mind-blowing, the deadly secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.07,0:00:19.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a place we call the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:25.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是银河系领域末日终结者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the apocalyptic finale of our galactic neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.70,0:00:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它也许是整个太阳系历史中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Probably the most dramatic event
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.48,0:00:29.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最壮观的景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the entire history of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.02,0:00:32.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经知晓这颗母星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've now uncovered sizzling clues
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.37,0:00:35.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即将猛烈活动直至死亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about our home star's violent demise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.56,0:00:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这结果似乎对地球极为不利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the outcome doesn't look good for planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:45.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许被热死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You could experience both death by fire
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:47.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许被冻死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and also death by ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.69,0:00:51.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新一代尖端科学发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}New cutting-edge science traces
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.82,0:00:54.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,待太阳释放出最后能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the real horrors awaiting our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.79,0:01:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极度恐慌就将降临到地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as our Sun unleashes its final fury.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.14,0:01:02.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一切均将灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The kiss of death for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.83,0:01:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.05,0:01:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经用光亮和能量孕育了我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's bathed us wth light and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.66,0:01:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,45亿余年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for over 4.5 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.37,0:01:28.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而像宇宙万物一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But like all things in the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的母星最终会走向灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our nurturing star will eventually die.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:41.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球也将随之逐渐消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Earth could literally melt into the sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.14,0:01:47.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克雷格·德福斯特\N美国西南研究院
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:46.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳光亮比现在增强一百倍时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun gets a hundred times brighter than it is now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.25,0:01:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个地球表面将化为灰烬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the entire surface of the Earth will be incinerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.04,0:01:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,组成陆地的岩石也将熔化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the rock that composes the continents will melt
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:55.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并汇合成为大面积熔岩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and run into seas of molten lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.12,0:01:58.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球将不再适宜居住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth will be uninhabitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.04,0:02:02.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳之死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The death of our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.43,0:02:06.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对宇宙影响深远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will have a profound effect on our cosmic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:09.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们依赖着母星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We rely on our home star,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.24,0:02:12.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它位于太阳系的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located in the center of our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.65,0:02:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个巨大熔岩球体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over one million Earths could easily fit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.46,0:02:20.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够轻松装下百万余个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inside this gargantuan ball of bubbling gas
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.03,0:02:25.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其内核温度达到三千万华氏度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with core temperatures reaching 30 million degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.84,0:02:30.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳距离我们大约九千三百万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is approximately 93 million miles away,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.24,0:02:34.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此地球表面冷热适宜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so Earth is not too hot or too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.15,0:02:38.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是形成液态海水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the perfect distance to sustain oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.92,0:02:42.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和多样生物的完美距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of liquid water and abundant life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.82,0:02:52.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.25,0:02:49.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的生存特别依赖于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're incredibly dependent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.96,0:02:52.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳所提供的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Sun's energy for our survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.33,0:02:56.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先  植物利用阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}First and foremost, plants utilize solar energy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.71,0:02:59.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进行光合作用  才能够生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in photosynthesis so that they can grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们利用植物获取食物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, we use plants for food
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.85,0:03:02.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其他动物也是如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so do other animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:04.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也食用那些动物的肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we eat those other animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.83,0:03:07.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还使用由腐烂植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We also use the fossil fuels
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.71,0:03:10.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转变来的矿物燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from partially decayed plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风能也是由太阳热量产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Winds are also generated by the Sun's heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.97,0:03:17.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们随处都在利用太阳能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're using solar energy everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:22.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些赋予生命的热能和光能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All this life-giving heat and light
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.76,0:03:24.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都来自于太阳内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes from the Sun's core,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:30.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里就像个巨大的核反应堆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a colossal nuclear reactor comprised of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:33.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,四分之三是氢气  余下为氦气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}three-quarters hydrogen and the rest mostly helium
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.41,0:03:35.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有少量重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with traces of heavier elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.30,0:03:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里  氢原子核组合形成氦原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, hydrogen nuclei combine to form helium nuclei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.08,0:03:48.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个过程称为聚变  能够释放辐射能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This process called fusion gives off radiant energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.38,0:03:54.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这辆车就好比刚生成时的恒星太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This car is like a newly formed star like the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:03:59.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳诞生时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a star like the Sun is born,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.93,0:04:02.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随之诞生的还有一整箱油\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's born with a full tank of gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.42,0:04:07.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我将油箱灌满\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if I fill this tank with gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:12.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像氢元素被吸引到一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's like the hydrogen coming together gravitationally,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:15.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,组成一个炙热高密度内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forming a hot, dense core.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.49,0:04:17.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,油继而燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That gas will later burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:18.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在恒星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the case of a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:21.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢元素将融合组成氦元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hydrogen will fuse to form helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:23.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向恒星供给能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}giving the star energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.16,0:04:26.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像油在车里燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as in the case of the gas burning in the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将提供车运动所需能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that'll give the car energy with which to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.17,0:04:32.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像一辆汽车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like an automobile,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.53,0:04:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳也会耗尽燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun will eventually run out of fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:40.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球也将失去这个赖以生存的能量之源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Earth will be without this crucial power source.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:44.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢元素聚合生成氦元素的不对称比例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rate at which it's fusing hydrogen into helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.58,0:04:47.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终会导致内核中氢元素耗尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will someday simply run out of hydrogen in its core.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:50.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这可以借鉴其他类似星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can see other similar stars
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:52.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们诞生时间早于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that were born much earlier than the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.41,0:04:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经逐渐消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're now dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.48,0:05:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了追踪太阳之死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To track our Sun's dark future,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:05.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们回到了它诞生之时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we travel back in time to its beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.84,0:05:14.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些奇异的气体云雾被称做星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These exotic clouds of gas and dust are called nebulas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.95,0:05:19.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由正在消亡的天体残余物组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They consist of the remnants of dying stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.33,0:05:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但根据最新研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But upon closer observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.35,0:05:25.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是孕育\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're actually stellar nurseries
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:28.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星的温床\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where stars like our Sun were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.80,0:05:37.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}道格·邓肯\N科罗拉多大学
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.81,0:05:34.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约四十五亿年前的银河系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 4 1/2 billion years ago in our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:37.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一团巨大的气体云雾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a giant cloud of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.17,0:05:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在引力的作用下逐渐聚集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gradually was pulled together by gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:43.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当引力作用使得星云崩溃时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as gravity caused that cloud to collapse,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量能量释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a lot of energy was released,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:47.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中心地带急速升温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it heated up and finally, in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,核反应开始促使氢元素转变为氦元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nuclear reaction started changing hydrogen into helium
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.49,0:05:53.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗新星就这样诞生了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a new star was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.80,0:05:59.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,余下的星际物质围绕新生太阳转动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The remaining stellar material swirled around the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.39,0:06:02.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生碰撞并接合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It collided and coalesced,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:04.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终形成太阳系的八个星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eventually sculpting the eight planets
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.57,0:06:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时包括地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our solar system including Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:11.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时  星风开始将\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When that happened, a stellar wind turned on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.63,0:06:13.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有其他物质清理干净\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and cleared out all the extra material
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.55,0:06:16.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只留下了我们现在所知的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving the planets that we have today
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:17.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和其他一些天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and additional bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:19.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中有些发生碰撞或与其他星球融为一体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some of which collided or merged with the other planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:25.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙无数的发光源之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among the billions of points of light in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:27.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳只是一个普通的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our Sun is an average star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.60,0:06:31.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有比它大一百倍的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are stars 100 times its mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳真实的颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And contrary to its appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:37.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与日升日落时呈现的颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the true color of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.13,0:06:40.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}differs from what we see when it rises and sets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:47.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳其实是个白色天体  并非黄色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is actually a white star, not a yellow star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:49.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白得像这辆车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's white like this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.54,0:06:52.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光谱的峰值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, it's true that the peak of its spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.40,0:06:54.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是黄色光波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is sort of in the yellow region,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也发出一些蓝光和绿光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it also emits some blue light and green light,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.78,0:06:59.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有橙色  红色光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and orange and red.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:01.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些颜色聚集在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all those colors together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:04.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被我们的视网膜和大脑所接收\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are perceived by our retina and our brain
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.35,0:07:05.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就成为白色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the color white.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:11.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳和我们人类有很多共同之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun has a lot in common with humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.86,0:07:13.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它年轻时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.88,0:07:17.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十分活跃毫无规律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was extremely active and often unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.48,0:07:22.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现它真是惊奇之物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we found was really very surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.48,0:07:24.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当类似太阳的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We found that stars like the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:25.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在年轻时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they're very young,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:28.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转速比现在快很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are rotating much, much faster than today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.45,0:07:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一颗飞速旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you can imagine something as big as the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自转周期只有一天或者更短的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just whipping around in one day or even less,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:36.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那可就大不一样了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was a very different kind of Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上面会发生各种爆炸与喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's having all kinds of eruptions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:43.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断地向地球发射出粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that blasted particles through space that hit the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:49.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如今  我们的太阳只是中年寿命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right now, our Sun is middle-aged
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:52.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运行平和  规律而稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and has settled into a quieter, regular schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.51,0:07:56.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时仍然释放着能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's still generating a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.11,0:08:01.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今的太阳  已经45亿岁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun, right now, is about 4 1/2 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:04.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎达到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's slightly under
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.00,0:08:08.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其既定寿命的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}half of its total anticipated lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.61,0:08:10.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就好像是这辆车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's kind of like this car
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,油箱里的油即将消耗一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a little bit more than half of its tank still full.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.52,0:08:18.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳以稳定然剧烈的速率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun now is burning fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:20.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,消耗燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is, fusing hydrogen to helium...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.11,0:08:23.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即氢氦核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a steady but ferocious rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就好像是一颗900亿吨级的炸弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like a 90 billion megaton bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:30.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接二连三不间歇地爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}going off every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:33.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是强大得不可思议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just an incredible amount of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.67,0:08:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,身居地球  事实上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth, we're actually only receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只接收到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about one 2-billionth of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.39,0:08:43.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳产生的能量的五亿分之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's being produced at the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:48.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以我们如今的科技水平\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, on a daily basis, that's enough energy to power
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.15,0:08:50.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}霍莉·吉尔伯特\N国家航空航天局戈达航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:50.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这足以支持2.9亿亿颗100瓦的灯泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 29 million billion
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.88,0:08:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时点亮一小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}100-watt light bulbs for one hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.94,0:08:56.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从太阳内部产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The amount of energy being generated
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.16,0:08:58.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实在是巨大得难以计量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the interior of the Sun is just enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.88,0:09:01.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将持续这种活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun will continue
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:03.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生产能量  并如此穷尽毕生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to churn out energy over its entire lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.48,0:09:08.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据估算  也就是还有120亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is estimated to be around 12 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:13.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,二十世纪九十年代  科学家们通过测算\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 1990s, scientists confirmed its age
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.23,0:09:14.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的亮度和初始质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when it will die
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.62,0:09:18.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时对其声波进行分析\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by measuring its brightness and original mass
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.82,0:09:22.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得出了它的年龄与确切死期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as analyzing its sound waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.08,0:09:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光线是无法通过太阳的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light doesn't penetrate the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.47,0:09:25.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它不透明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's opaque.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:27.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这听上去很奇怪  因为光线正是来自于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That sounds strange because light comes from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.40,0:09:29.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却无法穿过它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but light can't pass through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.65,0:09:31.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此直到近些年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So until recently, there was no way
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.39,0:09:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们才找到办法侦测太阳内部的深层地带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to probe the deep interior of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:36.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是种被称为的太阳地震学的科学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a science now called helioseismology
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.24,0:09:38.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用声波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that uses sound waves to actually probe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.35,0:09:39.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,侦测太阳内部结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the interior structure of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.98,0:09:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们因而才弄清楚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so we have a very good knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的内部结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what the interior structure of the star looks like,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.89,0:09:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且得以缩小范围和最终确定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's allowed us to constrain and confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:50.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的准确年龄与进化过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the models of the Sun's age and its evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.12,0:09:58.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奇怪的是  太阳比初生时亮度增加了30%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Strangely, our Sun is now 30% brighter than it was at birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.55,0:09:59.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着年岁的增长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.79,0:10:03.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还将变得更加明亮和强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will gradually grow even brighter and more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.69,0:10:09.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的气候对太阳能量的波动非常敏感\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our climate is very sensitive to the energy from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.73,0:10:11.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  如果你仍在操心人类的所作所为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you're worried about global warming,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.61,0:10:14.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对全球变暖的激烈影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you worry about what humans are doing to the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.51,0:10:15.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时也要明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but you also need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.84,0:10:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳也在干扰大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the Sun is doing to the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:23.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最新的估测结果指出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most recent estimate says that maybe 20%
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.27,0:10:25.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全球变暖20%的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of all the warming that's happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.11,0:10:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取决于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the global warming, is due to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:38.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十亿年后  地球表面能见度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In one-billion years, our star's luminosity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:41.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将增强10%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will be 10% greater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度也将上升100度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and temperatures on our planet will be 100 degrees hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空气中的水分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The moisture in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.14,0:11:01.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很好的吸收了红外线与热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is very good at trapping infrared radiation or heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.42,0:11:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就好像是给地球裹上了一层毛毯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so it's sort of like putting a blanket on the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由此带来的恶劣影响是这样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, here is the bad part.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:07.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着地球变暖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Earth warms up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.57,0:11:09.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋将加剧蒸发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the oceans evaporate even more,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:10.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致更多的热量被锁定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we trap more heat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.93,0:11:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后地球会加剧变暖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so the Earth warms up more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:15.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后当地球变暖加剧  再一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when the Earth warms up more, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.17,0:11:18.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更多的热量被锁定  恶性循环  循循不息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we trap even more heat and the effect can run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.62,0:11:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是温室效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's what we call the Greenhouse Effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.90,0:11:27.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脱缰的温室效应导致的气温飙升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With this surge of heat due to the runaway Greenhouse Effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.15,0:11:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关系地球上生物的生死存亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}life on Earth will be in peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.47,0:11:34.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,届时  所有的生物群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whole societies will need to retreat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:37.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将只好退避到地下遮蔽处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to underground shelters during the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有在夜晚气温降下的时候  才能走上地面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then emerge at night when the temperature cools down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:43.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而随着温度不断攀升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as the thermometer continues to climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:47.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终将无处可藏身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there eventually will be nowhere to run or hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.91,0:11:51.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终的结果是已知的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know how that story ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.33,0:11:53.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是  金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called the planet Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:55.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想想看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:12:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金星距离太阳只比地日距离短30%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus is only about 30% closer to the Sun than the Earth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.34,0:12:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是却热上很多  温度高达800度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's way, way, way hotter, 800 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.64,0:12:06.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前我们还没有掌握\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't quite have the technology that would allow us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.71,0:12:09.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够在金星表面生存的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to survive on the surface of Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:11.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是可以推断\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we could imagine what would be required,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:13.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,隔热是必要前提\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}insulating yourself from the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:15.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这将是个巨大挑战\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it would be a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:20.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 3 billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.10,0:12:23.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的亮度会增加40%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our Sun's brightness sill increase 40%.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:26.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至那时  海洋将被烤干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By this time, oceans will have boiled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球变成沙漠之球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth will have become a global desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会因氢氦核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun will have used up about three-quarters
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:40.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耗尽内部四分之三的氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the hydrogen in its core fused to helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.14,0:12:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就好像这辆车  已经消耗了四分之三的燃油\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like this car is three-quarters empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.63,0:12:46.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,届时  太阳会比如今明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By this time, the Sun will be brighter
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.93,0:12:49.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且体积也更大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than it is now and bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.76,0:12:51.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  地球会变得更热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So Earth will be hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.14,0:12:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而不再是生命的乐土\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't be a nice place to live at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:13:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而噩梦还远没有结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the solar nightmare is far from over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.46,0:13:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳寿命超过100亿岁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Sun nears its ten billionth birthday and beyond,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.53,0:13:11.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将发生终极质变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most drastic changes will occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.58,0:13:18.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳覆盖了整个地平线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If human-type civilizations are still around,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:22.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如若人类文化仍在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what will be the options for survival
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.36,0:13:26.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将何去何从\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when our Sun eventually fills the entire horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结局是注定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a foregone conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:38.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳达到100亿岁寿命的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun is about 10 billion years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.59,0:13:41.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会耗尽内部所有的氢燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will run out of hydrogen fuel in its core.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.99,0:13:45.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就吹响了这颗恒星的死亡号角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the beginning of the end for our star,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:48.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且  它不会静静地死去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it won't die peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.10,0:13:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对地球来说  全球变暖以及其他的各种灾祸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As for Earth, global warming or other cataclysms
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:03.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅10亿年后就将灭绝所有生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could snuff out every living thing in a mere 1 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.81,0:14:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就算那时  人类的后代找到了生存的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if human descendants somehow manage to survive until then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:12.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们面对的也是人间炼狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they could face a living hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.09,0:14:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳耗尽内核所有的氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun burns through all of its hydrogen at its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:23.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会开始紧缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will eventually start contracting on itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.95,0:14:25.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}霍莉·吉尔伯特\N国家航空航天局戈达航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:26.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为一旦氢的燃烧停止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's no longer burning through the hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.01,0:14:27.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,核聚变也将停止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fusing it together,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够与万有引力抗衡的放射压也会停止生成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating this radiation pressure outwards
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.42,0:14:31.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内缩的力便胜过了外扩的力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to balance the gravitational pull inwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:36.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳内核的氢聚变停止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While hydrogen fusion will stop in the core,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.53,0:14:39.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地壳的氢聚变将接过接力棒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will continue to fuse at a faster rate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.07,0:14:41.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以更高的速率进行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the shell surrounding the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.07,0:14:45.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多余的能量扩大太阳的外层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The extra energy will expand the outer layers of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:49.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这意味着太阳将变得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That'll mean that the Sun will grow
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:53.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:52.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更加能量十足  光亮耀眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much more powerful, much more luminous,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:55.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为太阳的内核收缩速率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the hydrogen shell will be fusing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.89,0:14:57.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会比往常快很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while the core is contracting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.74,0:15:00.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此氢壳将被熔化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a greater rate than it normally would.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.98,0:15:04.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢壳熔化产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the pressure from the energy generated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.12,0:15:06.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会生成压强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this hydrogen-fusing Shell
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而压强将使得太阳外部结构的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will cause the outer parts of the Sun to expand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.41,0:15:11.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而使太阳成为一颗红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Making it into a red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红巨星指的是一颗恒星已经\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A red giant is a star that has exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.50,0:15:19.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耗尽了其内部核心最初储备的氢能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the primary reservoir of hydrogen fuel at its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:24.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留下了正在形成的高浓度氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving behind a buildup of the heavier, denser helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.71,0:15:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗和太阳大小相似的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An average-sized star like our Sun will spend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:33.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会以红巨星的身份度过最后的二十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the final 2 billion years of its life as a red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.88,0:15:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们之所以称其为红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call it a red giant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.42,0:15:38.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为当恒星发生膨胀时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because as this expansion happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.26,0:15:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其表面积会增大很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the surface area gets so great
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:42.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表面温度也会降低\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it actually cools off and,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从温度的角度上说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in terms of temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星表面温度越低颜色就会越红\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stars that are cooler appear redder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:51.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在红巨星最初的形成阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the initial red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:54.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会有灾难性的变化发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}catastrophic changes will occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:58.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳将会膨胀到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun will swell to 20 to 30 times
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.17,0:15:59.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其原始体积的二十到三十倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its original size
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.83,0:16:03.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光照强度将会是现在的一百倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and become one-hundred times more luminous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.46,0:16:08.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳红巨星膨胀时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As our red giant Sun expands,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.36,0:16:11.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在相对静止的氦核周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will continue to vigorously fuse hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:14.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将持续猛烈的和氢气熔合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the shell surrounding the inactive helium core,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而在核中制造出更多的氦气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thus producing more helium in the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.35,0:16:21.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦一切真的发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:24.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的核心将会进一步瓦解  温度会更高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the core of the Sun collapses further and gets hotter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:26.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会在几十亿年间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Sun gradually expands
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.03,0:16:28.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐步的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over the course of a couple of billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.72,0:16:33.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克雷格·德福斯特\N西南研究院
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.06,0:16:31.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上  太阳核心的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, the core of the Sun is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.90,0:16:33.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经足够燃烧氦气了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hot enough to ignite the helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:35.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这被称为氦闪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You get what's called a helium flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.24,0:16:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就如同点燃燃气烤架时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like the stellar equivalent of the big woof
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.31,0:16:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一声扑哧的巨响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you light a gas barbecue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.66,0:16:45.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被点燃的氦气温度已经足够进行熔合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ignited helium will be hot enough to undergo fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.77,0:16:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而在核内产生了碳和氧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}now creating carbon and oxygen in the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:16:52.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即将陨落的太阳又能从\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The dying Sun will be resuscitated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:55.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短暂的新能量中得到恢复\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with this new but temporary form of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:08.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我被困在沙漠里并且汽车没油了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm stuck here in the desert, and I've run out of gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.24,0:17:14.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我在后备箱存有一加仑备用油\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, you know, I have a spare gallon here in the trunk,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我把油倒进油箱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and if I pour this gas into the gas tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:21.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么这辆车又能行驶很长一段路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that'll allow the car to keep going for a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.88,0:17:24.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这和太阳是同一个道理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is kinda similar to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:25.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在红巨星阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the red giant stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.72,0:17:28.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将把氢能源消耗殆尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's gonna run out of hydrogen as fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:31.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它将在数千万年内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it'll have helium that can briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.18,0:17:33.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生氦能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a few tens of millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:35.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔合之后生成的碳和氧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fuse to carbon and oxygen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.16,0:17:37.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又将为太阳提供新的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}providing a new source of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.29,0:17:40.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它能够继续运转很长一段时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that'll keep the Sun going for a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.44,0:17:46.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在红巨星初始阶段结束时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the end of the initial red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.51,0:17:50.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,陨落的太阳会进入一个稳定的氦燃烧阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the dying Sun will enter this stable helium-burning phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:54.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的温度将更高  体积会缩小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will become hotter yet somewhat smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.10,0:17:58.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这仅仅只是暴风雨来临前的平静罢了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this is merely a lull before the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.49,0:18:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为太阳进入的红巨星时期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is because the Sun's transition to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.82,0:18:07.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被分为两个阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a red giant actually comes in two phases.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.76,0:18:10.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当其处于第二阶段后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the second phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.60,0:18:13.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,核内的氦气将被耗尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the helium will be exhausted in the core,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.24,0:18:16.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而太阳的核将由碳和氧组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which will now consist of carbon and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.93,0:18:20.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此核将重新收缩和加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The core will again start to contract and heat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.17,0:18:23.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是氦气在太阳的外壳中仍有剩余\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But helium will still exist in the Shell,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.21,0:18:26.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会继续熔合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it will continue to fuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.13,0:18:29.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在收缩的核中制造更多的碳和氧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forming more carbon and oxygen in the contracting core
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这一切将被\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all of this will still be surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:33.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢壳包裹住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the hydrogen shell
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.83,0:18:36.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并继续和氦气熔合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's still fusing to helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.17,0:18:42.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳成为红巨星之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun becomes a red giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:43.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会膨胀开来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will expand out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:44.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将做的第一件事就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the first thing it'll do is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吞食水星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}engulf the planet Mercury
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:48.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上是燃烧它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eventually incinerate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.00,0:18:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使水星蒸发  完全吞食它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}evaporate it, eat it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.07,0:18:54.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接下来太阳会向金星膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then it'll expand out to Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.93,0:19:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}道格·邓肯\N科罗拉多大学
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.52,0:19:00.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在氦气转变为碳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After the helium changing into carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.03,0:19:02.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并耗尽所有能量后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}uses up all of its energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:05.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其内核将再次收缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the core begins to shrink a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:07.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳外部再次膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer part expands a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:08.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后开始变得极不稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's not very stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.73,0:19:12.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳红巨星处于第二阶段时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the second red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:15.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剧烈的收缩和膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wild contraction and expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.11,0:19:18.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会使太阳变得像一个缓慢跳动的心脏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will make our Sun pulsate like a slow-beating heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:23.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跳动会在每几百或几千年就发生一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsations can occur every few hundred or thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.84,0:19:26.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一次的跳动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and with each pulsation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.74,0:19:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都会使整个行星系统一片混乱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}planetary pandemonium will ensue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:33.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水星和金星都难逃厄运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mercury and Venus are doomed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.28,0:19:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们都将被红巨星吞食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They'll be engulfed by the red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.91,0:19:39.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是  在很多的科学文献中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, there's been some debate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.71,0:19:40.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也存在争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the scientific literature
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.70,0:19:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是否真的会被吞食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as to whether the Earth would actually be engulfed or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.81,0:19:47.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的太阳是足够吞食地球的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun will be large enough to engulf the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.81,0:19:50.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的生死未卜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth's future is uncertain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.98,0:19:52.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为地球就在存在于灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it lies on the borderline
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.86,0:19:55.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之间的界线之上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between being engulfed and surviving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在也有宇航员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But astronomers now have one possible sneak
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:03.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对地球的最终命运有一个恰当的预言\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}preview of our planet's ultimate fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:08.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红外线光学望远镜捕捉到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The infrared optical telescope array has captured
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:12.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗垂死恒星  天鹅座-X的特写镜头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}close-up photos of a death star, Chi Cygni,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:16.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它离地球约有五十光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is approximately 50 light-years from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.46,0:20:21.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天鹅座-X已经处于红巨星阶段的末尾了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Chi Cygni is near the end of its red giant stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:23.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它膨胀的足够大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it's grown really big.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.45,0:20:26.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其存在的几百万年间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in those last few million years of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.54,0:20:28.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会开始有规律的跳动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It starts pulsating.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:31.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上  它每四百年跳动一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It actually pulsates every 400 years or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.14,0:20:32.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,膨胀之后变得又大又亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Getting bigger and brighter
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:34.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收缩之后变得又小又暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and smaller and fainter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这个巨大膨胀的天鹅座-X\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the massively bloated star
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.66,0:20:40.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我们的太阳的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Chi Cygni were our Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.66,0:20:44.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将一直吞没每一颗行星直到火星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would have consumed every planet out to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.63,0:20:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球以及地球上所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth and all its wondrous forms of life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:49.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将被垂死之星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have been melded with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.95,0:20:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内部的物质所熔合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the materials inside the dying star.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:57.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的生命显然很短暂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We obviously haven't been around long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.51,0:20:58.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们有生之年看不到这些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and will not be in our lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以很难确切的知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to understand exactly what's gonna happen
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.97,0:21:02.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的陨落到底会发生什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the Sun dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:03.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们只有通过对其他恒星的观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we need to look to other stars
