Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.89,0:23:47.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说地球的轨道会逐渐远离太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that means that Earth's orbit gradually drifts away from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.63,0:23:51.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但实际上由于地球离太阳表面过近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's also true that Earth, being pretty close to the surface of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.53,0:23:56.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会使太阳上掀起一波波气浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will raise a tide, a bulge of gas on the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.17,0:23:59.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而气浪和地球之间的引力相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a gravitational interaction between that bulge
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:03.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会减慢地球的公转速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Earth will actually slow down the Earth in its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.12,0:24:06.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而使地球逐渐向轨道内侧旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}causing the Earth to gradually spiral in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.00,0:24:11.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳质量的减少可能使地球轨道安全外移\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So maybe the loss of mass will move us out enough to be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.30,0:24:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但产生的潮汐力可能把地球向内牵引\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But maybe the tidal forces will spiral us in enough
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.34,0:24:18.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以致地球可能被太阳吞没并燃为灰烬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we'll be engulfed and the Earth will be incinerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:22.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等五六十亿年后再回来看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if you come back in 5 or 6 billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.47,0:24:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就能知道鹿死谁手了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll know which one wins out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.45,0:24:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球可能是幸运的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth just might get lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.57,0:24:31.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个国际天文学家小组发现了太阳系外的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An international team of astronomers discovered a planet
