Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.66,0:24:42.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗系外行星的体积至少是木星的三倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The exoplanet is at least three times as massive as Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.77,0:24:47.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并绕着恒星391佩贾斯公转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and orbits the star dubbed 391 Pegasi,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.39,0:24:50.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该恒星与太阳体积相当\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is about the same mass as our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.96,0:24:55.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些系外行星经历了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some exoplanets clearly do survive
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.21,0:24:56.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其主星的红巨星阶段后仍能存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the red giant stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.94,0:25:02.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如391佩贾斯与其系外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, 391 Pegasi is a star that has an exoplanet around it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.23,0:25:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绕着它公转的这颗行星幸存了下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a planet orbiting it, and that planet is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.63,0:25:08.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗行星可能和地球一样有岩石核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, it might have a rocky Earth-like core
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.46,0:25:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至有铁质内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps even an iron central region.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.28,0:25:14.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们认为它很可能是气态或液态行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we think it's mostly gaseous and liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.16,0:25:19.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,391佩贾斯及其巨大的气体行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}391 Pegasi and its gas giant planet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.38,0:25:21.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之间的轨道距离和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have a similar orbital distance from each other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.80,0:25:23.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球与太阳之间的轨道距离非常相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as Earth does from our Sun,
