Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.20,0:25:55.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但与主星距离恰到好处的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But you would not expect to find a lot of planets
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.02,0:25:58.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不多见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in that particular range of distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.23,0:26:00.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数行星要么被主星完全吞没\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would expect them to either be completely swallowed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.46,0:26:02.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要么就远远地移开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or have them be much further out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.86,0:26:07.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此只有这两种力达到微妙的平衡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it requires a somewhat delicate balance of the two competing forces
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.15,0:26:10.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能使行星移动到安全范围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to actually enable a planet to survive at that sort of location.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.62,0:26:14.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由此看来  行星的幸存已有先例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's one case in which the planet survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.84,0:26:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不幸的是在这类似太阳系的星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bad news is that in this solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.18,0:26:20.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该行星的体积比木星的还要大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planet is really big, larger than Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.10,0:26:23.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它的幸存几率要比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so it probably has a better chance of surviving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.25,0:26:25.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球这样的小行星大得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than a small planet like the Earth would.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.89,0:26:30.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,391佩贾斯产生的恒星风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It appears that stellar winds
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.76,0:26:34.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和热力脉冲似乎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and thermal pulsations produced by 391 Pegasi
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.05,0:26:38.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使系外行星的大气表层物质在引力作用下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pulled atmospheric material from the outer layers of the exoplanet
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.97,0:26:40.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被释放到太空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hurled it into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.20,0:26:44.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而这颗气体巨星仍幸存了下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, the gas giant planet survived
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.13,0:26:48.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因所散失的质量在其可承受范围之内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it could afford to lose a lot of mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.34,0:26:51.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可推测该行星所散失物质的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can speculate that it may have lost
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.66,0:26:53.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于不止一个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one or more Earth masses of material.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.89,0:26:55.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很显然  如果地球散失了相当的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And of course, if the Earth lost that much material,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.90,0:26:56.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就不复存在了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.45,0:27:00.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然  与木星等大的气体巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Certainly, a Jupiter-sized planet, a gas giant
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.64,0:27:02.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不适合人类居住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}isn't inhabitable by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.52,0:27:06.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但令人感兴趣的是当太阳进入红巨星阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's still intriguing that if the Sun went to the red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.50,0:27:08.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星将可能是幸存下来的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's possible that Jupiter would survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.51,0:27:14.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绕391佩贾斯公转的气体巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The continued existence of the gas giant planet
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.37,0:27:19.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的存在无论如何都不能有力地说明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting 391 Pegasi doesn't provide conclusive evidence one way or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.13,0:27:23.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球能否在太阳的死亡后幸存下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether Earth will survive the death of our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.73,0:27:26.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但可以肯定的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But one thing seems certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.25,0:27:30.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早在太阳成为红巨星之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Long before our Sun becomes a red giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.07,0:27:34.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星球已不再适合地球生命的生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our planet will no longer be hospitable for Earth-type life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.80,0:27:38.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来的文明都必须在人间炼狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Any future civilizations will need to relocate,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.17,0:27:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成前数十亿年迁徙到其他星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and billions of years before the impending inferno.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.29,0:27:49.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今后大约十亿年的时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About a billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.52,0:27:53.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假如你们还活着  我建议你们移居火星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if viewers were around, I'd recommend that you move to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.77,0:27:57.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那时火星已经不像现在这么冷了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars, instead of being too cool like it is now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.23,0:28:00.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里的气温可能会更为适宜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would probably have a somewhat more favorable temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.21,0:28:03.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果火星地底有水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there is water underground in Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.01,0:28:05.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,且我们掌握了现在仍未知的某种技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we don't really know one way or the other for certain yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.99,0:28:07.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你们就可以好好利用这些水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe you could use some of that water
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.00,0:28:11.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并在火星上安享晚年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you might have a comfortable retirement on the planet Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.40,0:28:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要移居火星并非易事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the move to Mars wouldn't be simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.07,0:28:18.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来这颗红色行星虽会比现在更为温暖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The red planet would be warmer than it is today,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.04,0:28:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却仍缺少某些生命的必要元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it would still be missing a few of life's necessities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.42,0:28:27.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先要创造适宜的大气环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have to create an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.68,0:28:30.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接下来要制造足够的压力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have to have pretty high pressures in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.11,0:28:32.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以使地面上形成液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have molten water on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.01,0:28:35.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还要制造氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You need to somehow generate oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.66,0:28:39.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们说某颗行星或卫星是人类的可居住区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just because a planet or a moon is in the habitable zone
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.70,0:28:41.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不代表它们已可供居住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}doesn't mean that it's already habitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.79,0:28:45.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你是名策略规划师\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were a strategic planner,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.03,0:28:49.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能会设想十亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would encourage the growth of plant life on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.41,0:28:50.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在火星上种植植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a billion years in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.02,0:28:52.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以此制造氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would generate oxygen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.73,0:28:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使火星更适合人类居住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you'd make that planet more hospitable for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.02,0:28:59.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许稍微自负点说  我们称之为地球化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps, a little egotistically, we call that terraforming,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.88,0:29:05.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够创造出另一个类似地球的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That we could form another planet in the shape of Terra or the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.87,0:29:07.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我希望我们可以着手于此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I hope we're here to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.55,0:29:13.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使高度文明的社会成功殖民到火星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even if an advanced society manages to colonize Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.49,0:29:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个新家也只会是暂时的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This new home will be temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.20,0:29:19.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}适合居住区
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.35,0:29:19.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会继续变得更大更亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun will continue to become brighter and bigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.87,0:29:23.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将宜居地带不断向外推出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pushing the habitable zone ever farther out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.50,0:29:28.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在红巨星阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During the red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.39,0:29:30.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球人又得搬家了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earthlings will have to move again,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.97,0:29:35.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许搬到木星或者土星某个含水量多的卫星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps to the water-rich moons of Jupiter or Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.13,0:29:38.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但每到一个新地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But with every new location,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.11,0:29:40.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都将遇到更多的艰难险阻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There will be more obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.85,0:29:44.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到太阳的红巨星阶段临近结束时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Near the end of the Sun's red giant stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.30,0:29:48.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会急剧变大变亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will rapidly be growing much brighter and much bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.06,0:29:53.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们搬到新的宜居带将更为频繁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we'll need to move to the new habitable zone much more frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.78,0:29:57.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,搬到一个新的行星或卫星上的另一个问题是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another problem with moving to a new planet or a moon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.41,0:29:59.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运送所有人浪费的财力以及\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is that it would be very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.30,0:30:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遇到的困难都将会是巨大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and expensive to move all humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.81,0:30:03.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么你会怎么选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So whom do you choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.50,0:30:06.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只运送一些社会的精英吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just some elite subset of society?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.32,0:30:08.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那会造成更大的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would create great problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.25,0:30:13.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了在太阳成为红巨星前遗弃地球之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead of abandoning Earth before the Sun becomes a red giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.00,0:30:19.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个选择是移动地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another alternative might be to actually move the entire planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.64,0:30:21.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这可能听起来有点像科幻小说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This may sound like science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.01,0:30:24.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但相关的技术已经被考虑到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But technologies are already being considered
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.99,0:30:29.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能将地球从太阳的灾难中拯救出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That might rescue Earth from the solar apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.83,0:30:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将会灭亡的预测已经被广泛接受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Predictions about our Sun's demise are widely accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.35,0:30:42.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在大约五十亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In about 5 billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.60,0:30:46.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将会开始漫长的剧烈的死亡期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our star will begin a long, violent death.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.62,0:30:50.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它迅速成为红巨星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it mushrooms into a red giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.15,0:30:56.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会湮没水星金星以及很有可能地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will vaporize planets Mercury, Venus and most likely Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.40,0:31:02.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果人类文明仍然存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If human-type civilizations still exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.69,0:31:06.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们肯定已经搬到了太阳系之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They will have already relocated to the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.26,0:31:10.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们甚至可能连地球也一起搬出来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they may have even hauled Earth away with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.86,0:31:15.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难题是要找到恰当的宇宙推车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The challenge will be finding the right cosmic moving van.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.23,0:31:19.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有可能慢慢移动地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We might gradually move the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.61,0:31:23.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.57,0:31:23.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到一个新的宜居带  比如说通过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To a new habitable zone by, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.10,0:31:27.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将一颗小行星带到某个轨道上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taking an asteroid and bringing it into an orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.19,0:31:30.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好让它能每隔一段时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it comes reasonably close to the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.03,0:31:34.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠近地球并给地球一个向外移动的力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every once in a while and gives it a gravitational tug outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.94,0:31:39.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在科学家正在进行电脑模拟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right now, scientists are running computer simulations
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.28,0:31:42.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来论证用人工或无人驾驶的火箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to test the feasibility of actually moving Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.54,0:31:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,移动地球的可能性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using manned or drone rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.75,0:31:47.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了实现那个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.04,0:31:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}霍莉·吉尔伯特\N国家航空航天局戈达航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.76,0:31:50.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也许得用太阳帆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would either have to use solar sails, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.23,0:31:52.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来引导小行星进入正确的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to direct this asteroid into the correct place,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.66,0:31:54.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者用混合燃料的火箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or maybe a fusion-powered rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.98,0:31:57.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在十亿年之后我们可能拥有其他技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a billion years we may have other technologies that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.94,0:31:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以更容易做到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are much easier...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.90,0:32:01.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道到时候我们能做什么呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and who knows what we can do by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.17,0:32:05.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究表明小行星在太阳成为红巨星前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Researchers have determined that an asteroid
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.51,0:32:09.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必须每隔六千年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would need to be rounded up every 6,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.44,0:32:14.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将地球向外拉一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to keep nudging our planet outward as our Sun grows in brightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.42,0:32:18.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它很慢很平稳地拉地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it does that very gradually, very steadily,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.93,0:32:20.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超过好几百万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:23.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我们就会逐渐移动出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then we will gradually drift out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.16,0:32:26.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与宜居带的扩张保持同步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}keeping pace with the drifting habitable zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.71,0:32:32.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就算地球能在危险带以外继续绕太阳运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even if Earth could be re-orbited beyond the danger zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.31,0:32:34.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来的阳光也是阴暗的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its future remains bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.93,0:32:38.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到红巨星第二阶段末尾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Near the end of the second red giant phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.70,0:32:41.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的剧烈运动将会停息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the unstable pulsations of our Sun will subside
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.96,0:32:46.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它的大部分外层大气物质已经喷射出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because much of its outer atmosphere will be ejecting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.22,0:32:52.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后这意外着它的能量将会逐渐枯竭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, this means its energy will be rapidly depleting.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.24,0:32:54.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳质量不会那么大了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There won't be as much mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.93,0:32:58.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为巨大的引力挤压稀薄的氦气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as much gravity pushing down on the thin helium layer
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.51,0:32:59.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并将其压缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and compressing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.77,0:33:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就不会像之前一样对温度如此敏感了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it won't be as sensitive to the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.09,0:33:07.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个阶段  太阳实际上变得更小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this stage, the Sun will actually become smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.16,0:33:11.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更热更蓝  而不是不断向外膨胀的红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hotter and bluer, not red and big and extended.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.45,0:33:15.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以核反应频率将会下降\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so the nuclear reaction rates are going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.99,0:33:19.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}布拉德·海森\N加州大学洛城分校
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.56,0:33:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终  当恒星是去足够的质量后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So eventually, when the star has lost enough mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.37,0:33:22.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些核反应就基本消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those reaction rates basically die away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.74,0:33:24.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以该恒星  这里是太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the star, in this case the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.96,0:33:27.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将最终能源耗竭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will eventually run out of fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.40,0:33:29.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并开始收缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it will start to shrink.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.55,0:33:32.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不像其他恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike other stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.62,0:33:35.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳能源耗竭时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our dying Sun will not go out with a bang
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.59,0:33:37.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会发生爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it runs out of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.51,0:33:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些恒星死亡时会产生超新星爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some death stars actually produce a supernova explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.19,0:33:49.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸的光会瞬时照亮整个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a burst of radiation that can temporarily outshine an entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.90,0:33:52.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但为什么我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But why won't our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.45,0:33:56.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死亡时不会有如此绚丽呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have a spectacular fireworks display upon its death?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.80,0:34:01.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这正是某个观众想要问的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what one viewer wanted to ask the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.82,0:34:05.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自罗德岛纽波特的里洛伊·G发信息给我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so Leroy G. From Newport, Rhode island, texted us
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.39,0:34:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{/an8}为什么太阳死亡时不会发生超新星爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.56,0:34:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里洛伊  我很高兴地确信太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Leroy, I'm sure glad the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.30,0:34:13.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会发生超新星爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}won't explode as a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.32,0:34:14.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有两点理由\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.80,0:34:18.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先  太阳质量不足以产生爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}First, the Sun isn't massive enough to explode on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.51,0:34:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星必须要有太阳的八至十倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars have to be 8 or 10 times
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.66,0:34:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的质量才能发生爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mass of the Sun to explode on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.13,0:34:27.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外  太阳没有伴星供它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And second, the Sun doesn't have a companion star
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.38,0:34:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,获得物质  增大质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from which it could steal material, grow in mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.78,0:34:33.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终变得不稳定并爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eventually become unstable and explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.42,0:34:41.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳生命的最后阶段  它的外层大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the last stage of our Sun's life, its outer atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.61,0:34:44.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种会发光的被称作行星状星云的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a glowing sphere of gas called a planetary nebula,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.86,0:34:46.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will have drifted away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.26,0:34:50.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们一度很强大的太阳仅剩下的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All that will remain of our once powerful star
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.13,0:34:55.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是个白热的发光的星体叫做白矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will be a glowing white-hot cinder called a white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.63,0:34:58.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到那时它的体积将会同地球一般大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will be about the size of the Earth at that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.28,0:35:01.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克雷格·德福斯特\N西南研究院
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.08,0:35:02.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量也只有原来的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it'll have about half of its mass remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.51,0:35:08.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该星体仍然同原来的太阳一样热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That object still has as much thermal energy as the entire Sun did,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.64,0:35:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但体积很小且不能像原来一样有效地发出光来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's very small and doesn't radiate it very effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.47,0:35:15.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白矮星体积小但密度极大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}White dwarfs are small but extremely dense.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.79,0:35:19.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象我们太阳成为白矮星后同地球一样大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine our white dwarf Sun as small as the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.26,0:35:22.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但质量却和一颗恒星一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But with the same mass as a whole star.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.58,0:35:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你从白矮星上取下一块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were to take a chunk of white dwarf material
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.65,0:35:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,手机般大小的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same size as a cell phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.54,0:35:29.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会像大象一样重\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would weigh approximately the same
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.13,0:35:31.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以说该物质的密度是很大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as an elephant so it's very dense material
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.60,0:35:33.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管白矮星的体积\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although this white dwarf size
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.48,0:35:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同今天我们所见的太阳相比很小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is very small, relative to the Sun as we know it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:40.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为白矮星后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a white dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.68,0:35:42.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳就进入退休阶段了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our Sun will slip into retirement,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.88,0:35:47.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,消耗它表面积蓄的热量达数十亿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using up its life savings of thermal energy for billions,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.40,0:35:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至数万亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even trillions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.08,0:35:52.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它成为一颗白矮星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it has become a white dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.70,0:35:55.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就像是辆沿海岸前行的汽车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll be like a car that's coasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.30,0:35:58.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耗尽汽油后还在行驶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's run out of gas, but it's still moving
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.62,0:36:02.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它还有热运动能量推到它前进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it has energy of motion that's propelling it forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.18,0:36:06.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它并不会通过燃烧汽油产生新能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not generating any new energy by burning fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.77,0:36:12.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是会将内部储存的能量散发出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll be radiating away the stored energy in its hot interior,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.77,0:36:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它年轻有活力时通过核反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Energy that it had generated through nuclear reactions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.42,0:36:18.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was young and vibrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.81,0:36:20.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它就像这辆车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's like a car
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.23,0:36:23.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有汽油还在行驶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's just going along without any fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.31,0:36:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到最后  十分缓慢地停下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until finally, eventually, very slowly, it comes to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.36,0:36:35.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳演变成白矮星后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Anything left in the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.03,0:36:39.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系中剩下的一切物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after that transition to the white dwarf stage
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.10,0:36:40.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都会逐渐冷却下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would just gradually cool off.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.94,0:36:43.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们仍会围绕白矮星运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would remain in orbit around the white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.64,0:36:46.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运行轨道几乎不会发生变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The orbital decay times are extremely long,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.38,0:36:47.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如同一个冰冷萧索的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it would just stay there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.75,0:36:50.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日复一日地在轨道上盘旋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a quiet, cold orbiting body forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.28,0:36:56.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为白矮星的太阳会日益冰冷黯淡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our white dwarf Sun will become progressively cooler and dimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.95,0:36:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于太阳不再产能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since it's no longer generating energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.29,0:37:03.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系内的一切都会被冰封\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everything in the solar system will begin to freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.03,0:37:08.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着太阳的生命体征逐渐衰弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Sun's vital signs continue to dim,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.63,0:37:12.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的命运又会如何呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what will be the forecast for Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.97,0:37:21.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日渐年迈的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In its death throes,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.82,0:37:24.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,临终前也要挣扎一番\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our aging Sun will become insufferably hot
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.83,0:37:26.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先变成酷热难当的红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a red giant
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.54,0:37:30.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随后则是冰冷难耐的白矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then unbearably cold as a white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.38,0:37:34.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对地球来说  从火到冰的洗礼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This could be the kiss of death for planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.32,0:37:38.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仿佛是与死神来了次拥吻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it moves from the frying pan and into the frost.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.06,0:37:45.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}霍莉·吉尔伯特\N国家航空航天局戈达航天中心
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.14,0:37:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到太阳成为白矮星的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the time the Sun becomes a white dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.33,0:37:45.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以想象那时地球的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can imagine that temperatures on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.30,0:37:47.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,根据它所处于不同的轨道位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depending on where it is in its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.20,0:37:49.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会以一个惊人的速度显著下降\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would drop significantly fairly rapidly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.85,0:37:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为白矮星不再通过聚变产能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the white dwarf is no longer producing energy through fusion
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.74,0:37:56.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  它不再产能供给地球所需的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it's not producing this energy to heat the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.38,0:38:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果地球在太阳红巨星阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'll be fried to a crisp
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.67,0:38:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.41,0:38:05.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持它的轨道不变  我们就会被热焦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we remain where we are during the red giant stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.24,0:38:07.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in a similar vein,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.00,0:38:09.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果在白矮星时地球仍处于这个轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we will go into a deep freeze
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.94,0:38:14.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们就会被冻僵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we remain where we are when the Sun becomes a white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.56,0:38:15.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过  生命在某些区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nevertheless, there will be some pockets
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.96,0:38:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仍可以延续下去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where life could continue to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.65,0:38:21.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如  在海洋深处的液态区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, in the liquid parts deep in the oceans,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.63,0:38:22.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命能幸免于难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it could survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.57,0:38:26.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,理论上来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the outset,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.31,0:38:28.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一开始人类可以住进潜艇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}humans could theoretically live in submarines,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.94,0:38:31.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在靠近热液火山口的区域生活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near hot hydrothermal vents,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.64,0:38:33.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们能从深处的地核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while they dredge up the geothermal energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.80,0:38:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提取地热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from deep within the Earth's core.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.65,0:38:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是一百万年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But after a million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.65,0:38:41.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋彻冻结底\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the oceans would completely freeze
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.86,0:38:45.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命不可避免地走向灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and life would inevitably perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.03,0:38:49.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳变成白矮星后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After the Sun becomes a white dwarf,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.63,0:38:52.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会越来越冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's just gonna cool and cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.37,0:38:54.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这很像炉子上的锅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's very much like a pot on the stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.58,0:38:57.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}道格·邓肯\N科罗拉多大学
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.52,0:38:58.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你关闭了燃嘴  它就失去了能量来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once you turn off the burner, there's no more source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.37,0:39:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度逐渐降低  降低  再降低\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so it just gradually gets cooler and cooler and cooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.65,0:39:06.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果当太阳仅仅是一颗白矮星的时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the Earth manages to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.03,0:39:09.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球还幸免于难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until the Sun is only a white dwarf star,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.25,0:39:11.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那时将很难获取任何能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will hardly be getting any energy at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.02,0:39:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我可以十分确信地说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I can say with absolute certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.45,0:39:16.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你活得够长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that if you stick around long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.76,0:39:19.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便能经历火的炼狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could experience both death by fire
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.51,0:39:22.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与冰的洗礼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and also death by ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.26,0:39:26.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,失去了太阳释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without energy from our Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.13,0:39:29.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系幸存的生命都将灰飞烟灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all remaining life in our solar system will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.27,0:39:34.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而  我们可以通过目前无法实现的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, this disaster could be preempted
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.17,0:39:38.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,预先阻止这场灾难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by accomplishing what so far has been impossible to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.53,0:39:43.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是在地球上复制太阳的氢聚变反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually duplicating the Sun's hydrogen fusion right here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.42,0:39:51.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,控制核聚变的产生与进行已在科学能力所及\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science has already been able to manufacture nuclear fission,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.25,0:39:55.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它能使重原子核分裂成更轻更小的轻原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which involves the splitting of atoms into lighter, smaller nuclei.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.89,0:40:02.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正是这股力量驱动了我们的核电站\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the power that drives our nuclear power plants
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.50,0:40:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并由此激生了核武器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ignites nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.24,0:40:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而  在太阳核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But nuclear fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.67,0:40:13.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进行的核裂变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which occurs in the core of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.83,0:40:18.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要将轻原子聚合生成更大更重的原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}requires putting nuclei together to form a larger, heavier nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.78,0:40:22.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到目前为止  这项技术还没在地球上实现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so far, this process has not been achieved here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.62,0:40:26.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重造一个太阳环境最根本的难点是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem with recreating the Sun's conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.20,0:40:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}布拉德·海森\N加州大学洛城分校
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.06,0:40:28.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让物质拥有太阳核心处的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is essentially getting materials to the densities
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.79,0:40:31.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物质密度和温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and temperatures that you have in the center of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.59,0:40:35.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳自身的引力使压力与密度达到很高的水准\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun has its gravity to drive the pressures and densities up,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.86,0:40:37.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它可以进行这些高级反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it can get these high reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.80,0:40:40.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球上  人类不能奢望利用太阳的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth, we don't have the luxury of using the Sun's gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.50,0:40:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此  我们必须找到其它方法试着压缩物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we have to find other ways to try and compress the material
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.87,0:40:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而产生足够大的密度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and generate the kinds of densities that you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.61,0:40:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在加州北部的劳伦斯利弗莫尔国家实验室中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the Lawrence Livmore national laboratory in northern California,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.75,0:40:55.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们正进行一次挑战\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists are taking on the challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.18,0:40:58.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们试图创造一颗微缩人造恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by attempting to create a miniature man-made star.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.85,0:41:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这项实验包括将有三个足球场大小的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The experiment involves aiming the world's largest laser...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.82,0:41:06.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上规模最大的激光器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the size of three football fields...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.76,0:41:10.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞄准一个满载氢燃料的BB子弹大小的目标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a BB-sized target filled with hydrogen fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.20,0:41:14.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一个惯性约束实验中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In an inertial confinement experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.12,0:41:15.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像劳伦斯利弗莫尔的这次实验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like the one at Lawrence Livermore,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.55,0:41:17.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你需要一颗小圆球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you start with a small pellet,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.30,0:41:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的直径大概有半英寸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe a half an inch across,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.84,0:41:21.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中心填充着固体材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the core of which is made of a solid material
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.71,0:41:24.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由聚变所需的氢组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}containing lots of hydrogen to undergo fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.81,0:41:27.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,外层包裹着几层不同的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outside of which has layers of different material
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.84,0:41:29.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}克雷格·德福斯特\N西南研究院
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.54,0:41:29.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种设计使它们能产生冲击波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are engineered to produce a shock wave
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.35,0:41:33.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽可能地进入并挤压内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that will drive in and compress that core as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.66,0:41:39.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强激光束将散射成192小束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The colossal laser will split into 192 separate beams
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.29,0:41:42.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,轰击舱内的小球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that will strike the pellet housed inside a capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.53,0:41:46.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当燃料丸的外壳接触到高能X射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the fuel pellet's shell is struck by these high energy x-rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.20,0:41:47.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便会发生爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it should implode
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.47,0:41:51.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终  在核内产生核聚变反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then ultimately produce nuclear fusion in its core.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.11,0:41:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们掌握了可控廉价的核聚变技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we had controlled, affordable nuclear fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.74,0:41:57.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将改变一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would change everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.11,0:41:59.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们生活的方方面面都将变得不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many things about our lives would change.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.28,0:42:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最重要的是  我们将不再需要太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But most importantly, we wouldn't need the Sun anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.75,0:42:05.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能随心所欲地生产能量  热量和光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could produce energy, heat, light on demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.82,0:42:09.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有了氢的供给  便能生产我们所需的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could live anywhere in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.52,0:42:12.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类便能立足于宇宙的任何一个角落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a supply of hydrogen and make our own energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.83,0:42:19.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以迅速飞往其它行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could fly to other planets very quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.83,0:42:22.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只用几天时间  而不再是几年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in days instead of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.10,0:42:26.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你几乎可以从任何含有氢氧元素的物质中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can extract all the water you need from practically any material
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.21,0:42:28.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提取所需的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that contains hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.18,0:42:30.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果周围没有充足的氧气  你可以自己生产\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there isn't enough oxygen around, you could make some.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.75,0:42:36.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生稳定的核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Generating reliable nuclear fusion could
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.42,0:42:39.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将消除我们对太阳的依赖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ultimately save Earth and all forms of life
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.37,0:42:44.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并最终拯救地球和所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by eliminating our dependence on the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.26,0:42:50.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而  太阳自身的命运却已注定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet the Sun's own fate is forever sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.20,0:42:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是成为一颗日益黯淡阴冷的白矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a white dwarf, it will become dimmer and cooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.47,0:43:00.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗曾经为整个太阳系提供能量的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The star that once provided energy to an entire solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.37,0:43:03.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终将从人们的视野中淡去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will eventually fade from sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.81,0:43:11.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳最终冷却到一定程度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun eventually cools off so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.62,0:43:15.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它甚至无法被你的肉眼观测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you won't even be able to see it with your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.13,0:43:19.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这也是为什么有些人称它为黑矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so that's why some people call it a black dwarf
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.59,0:43:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或暗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or a dark star.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.36,0:43:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它无影于无形  静止于太空  流传于永恒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll just be invisible, sitting there in space nearly forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.67,0:43:35.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在五十亿年里  太阳系将注定迎来它的末日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our solar system cannot dodge its date with doom in 5 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.58,0:43:38.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但一个星系的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the death of one planetary system
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.38,0:43:41.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能唤起另一个星系的新生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can spark the birth of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.55,0:43:44.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的星云最终将和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun's nebula will eventually blend together
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.55,0:43:46.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其它星际物质交融\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with other stellar material
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.62,0:43:50.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,孕育出下一代恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and spawn the next generation of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.62,0:43:53.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许在它的呵护下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one might even nurture
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.66,0:43:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个生机勃勃的地球终将出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another vibrant planet like Earth.
